		<div class='component-usage' id='component-positioning'>
			<h2>Positioning</h2>
			<p>All notifications are fixed positioning that way they will always be visible to users on the screen. By default, the notification will be positioned in the bottom right of the screen. To override this default configuration, we can pass in string values to the notifications constructor for the X-position and the Y-positition. If you wish for the notification to not be positioned at all, you can pass in false for the aligned option in the configuration object. Since the notifications have a default position, the aligned option is by default set to true.</p>

			<p>The values that the configuration object will accept are 'right' or 'left' for the X-position, and 'top' or 'bottom' for the Y-position. Below you will see an example of all of these and how to incorporate multiple different notifications</p>

			<div class='component-html'>
				<pre>
					<code class='language-markup'>
&lt;div class='notification-container-1'&gt;
     &lt;h2 class='notification-title'&gt;Title&lt;/h2&gt;
     &lt;p class='notification-text'&gt;Bottom Left&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class='notification-container-2'&gt;
     &lt;h2 class='notification-title'&gt;Title&lt;/h2&gt;
     &lt;p class='notification-text'&gt;Top Right&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class='notification-container-3'&gt;
     &lt;h2 class='notification-title'&gt;Title&lt;/h2&gt;
     &lt;p class='notification-text'&gt;Top Left&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class='notification-4'&gt;
      &lt;h2 class='notification-title'&gt;Title&lt;/h2&gt;
      &lt;p class='notification-text'&gt;Unaligned&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
				   </code>
				</pre>
			</div>

